Here is the analysis for the TableOpsResources.garbageCollect endpoint.

- Full HTTP request path (starts with / and uses {} for path parameters when present)
  - /api/v0/ops/tables/garbagecollect
  - There are no path parameters in this endpoint (no variables in the path itself). The tombstoneOption value is supplied as a query parameter, not a path parameter.

- Are all HTTP methods acceptable?
  - No. The endpoint is defined only with @POST, so not all HTTP methods are acceptable.

- HEAD
  - Not acceptable based on the code. There is no @HEAD method defined for this path, and the endpoint does not provide a way to respond to HEAD requests beyond what is defined by the POST handler.

- POST

- OPTIONS

- TRACE

- GET

- PUT

- DELETE

- PATCH

Explanation:
- The endpoint lives in a class annotated with @Path("/api/v0/ops/tables"), and the specific method uses @POST @Path("/garbagecollect"), making the full path /api/v0/ops/tables/garbagecollect.
- The method is strictly a POST handler and uses a @QueryParam tombstoneOption along with a KeyspaceRequest body. There are no other HTTP method handlers (@GET, @PUT, @DELETE, etc.) for this path, and no @HEAD/@OPTIONS/@TRACE/@PATCH methods are defined. Therefore only POST is supported by the code.
